title: suggesting a pull-request-template.
body:
<!-- Thanks for submitting this pull request for KeY -->
<!-- Since the project has a strict review policy, please make the -->
<!-- reviewer's job easier by providing the necessary information -->
<!-- in the text below. The comments may remain since they will be -->
<!-- invisible when showing the PR. -->

## Intended Change
There is no guided process for writing PRs. But there should be. Therefore: Suggesting this template here.

## Reason for the pull request

improving git/github maintenance workflow.

## Touched elements

adding file to `.github`.
     
## Information for the reviewer
    
I tested that a file in this place should in the future appear as pull-request template on an empty repo of my own. I assume it will work here to.

title: Fix non duplicate feature perf
body:
I optimized the non duplicate app feature calculation by caching a map `rule name => [RuleApp]`.
This lead to an overall performance gain of about 20% for most cost computations done by the strategies.

I made some assumptions about `Node` that are not guaranteed by the interface (although I think they should be and `Node` could easily be made immutable).
See the doc of `getRuleAppsWithName`.

Two more things I noticed: 
* `NonDuplicateAppFeature::containsRuleApp` is always inverted
* Inverting the method to "does not contain" makes the code equal to `noDuplicateFindTaclet`, so I called this one instead

Is this really the case? `NonDuplicateAppFeature::filter` does a (now useless) case distinction over whether the position in occurrence is null and calls one of the two methods... It would be very odd if they did the same thing. Why would it be there if they were?

title: Proof tree view: Multiple small changes for readability
body:
I've digged these changes up from my main branch from over a year ago and made them cleaner.

* Cleanup some of the code
* Speed up ProofTreeSearchBar by caching the search strings (Makes a huge difference for large proofs)
* Fix example dialog loading previously hidden example on double-click on a folder

body:
Changes to CI pipeline for uploading the HTML test report generated by Gradle.

It also disables the failing (on external PR) test reporter action.
